#OpenXDK
http://openxdk.sourceforge.net/

OpenXDK is an open development environment to create applications on the original Microsoft Xbox. 
This project was originally started by Aaron Robinson (caustik) in 2002.

In summary, OpenXDK has the following features:

* Working libc layer (fopen, malloc, times, etc).  alloca is not supported.
* Multimedia support via SDL
* Gamepad controller support
* Audio support
* graphic hardware acceleration via pbKit
  
For more documentation, see the doc directory. You might also check out the official homepage at http://openxdk.sourceforge.net/
